      "side": 1,
      "message": "Before this: could you add an assertion that sensor-\u003eserialized_len \u003c sizeof(sensor-\u003eserialized) ?\nAs I understand snprintf, if the string would be larger than n-1, it is truncated to n-1, and a \\0 is added.  So if the return value is n, you can\u0027t tell whether it happened to be exactly n-1, or whether it was truncated.  Best to assert, that we don\u0027t get to this situation, it seems to me.",
