      "writtenOn": "2016-06-20T22:54:39Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "One might wonder if \"-1\" is enough here -- naively, you might think that this code should, say, try to get the frequency to run at, say, 110% of what was requested.  I guess the argument is that the extra overhead introduced by the emulator is very likely to consume less than a 1 ms, so the waiting the constant 1 ms is OK.  If this is the right argument (vs. the multiplicative factor idea), then maybe spell this out in the comment.  (It might be nice to change the local var \"delay\" to \"delay_ms\" -- variables specifying their units is always a good convention.)",
